Charles Saatchi's accountant Rahul Gajjar said he did not check the statements for Coutts credit cards given to the pair 'line by line'.

The Grillo sisters are accused of committing fraud by abusing their positions by using a company credit card for personal gain.

Prosecutors claim the Italian sisters lived the 'high life', spending the money on designer clothes and handbags from Louis Vuitton, Christian Dior and Vivienne Westwood.

The pair, of Bayswater, west London, deny the charge against them.

